    l5p:standing l5p:InProgress ;
    l5p:currentCeiling "First-ever adjudication (2026-07-21, cell-f census). cap03 (deterministic regen) -- holds live: a real root `ggen sync run --dry-run` against this checkout today reports all 5 of this pack's outputs (`.github/workflows/publish-candidate.yml`, `.github/workflows/marketplace-docs.yml`, `RELEASE_STANDING.json`, `RELEASE_STANDING.md`, `docs/PUBLICATION_JUDGMENT.md`) as `skipped: unchanged: content identical`; `composed_packs_e2e.rs` (2/2 passing, re-run live in this reconciliation pass) independently confirms idempotence as part of a real 30/31-pack union, though its own spot-check list covers 6 OTHER packs, not this one. Correction to cell-f's original census (this reconciliation pass independently re-ran the claim rather than trusting either the cell or the wave's own auditor): the pack's only dedicated proof, `crates/ggen-engine/tests/ggen_release_pack_workflow_e2e.rs` (the sole test anywhere naming PublishCandidateWorkflow/RELEASE_STANDING/PUBLICATION_JUDGMENT/marketplace-docs.yml), is GREEN, not red. Cell-f's original report claimed '0/2 -- currently RED' with an `[FM-CONFIG-002]` schema-dispatch failure; that specific claim did NOT reproduce and is corrected here rather than passed through. The wave's independent auditor re-ran it 3 times fresh against a clean build and got 2/2 every time; this reconciliation pass independently re-ran it 3 more times on top of that (6 consecutive green runs total, across two independent sessions) -- `marketplace_docs_workflow_regenerates_byte_identical_to_committed_file` and `marketplace_docs_workflow_second_sync_is_idempotent` both pass consistently, no FM-CONFIG-002 seen. Per this repo's own CLAUDE.md note that builds can flap nondeterministically under concurrent worktree sessions, the most plausible account is a transient environment artifact specific to cell-f's own worktree session at the time -- not a diagnosed code defect, and not reproducible now. cap05 (generated verification) -- the pack's clearest, most severe REAL gap, independently reconfirmed this pass: of 5 real outputs, only marketplace-docs.yml has any dedicated, exercised proof coverage; publish-candidate.yml is named only in a doc-comment inside ggen_release_pack_workflow_e2e.rs, never actually asserted against by either of its 2 real test functions, and RELEASE_STANDING.json, RELEASE_STANDING.md, docs/PUBLICATION_JUDGMENT.md have ZERO references anywhere in crates/*/tests/. No test is generated FROM the ontology either (no sparql: frontmatter deriving expected values -- same structural gap already disclosed for tcps-release-pack/star-toml-pack pre-cap05-closure). cap01 (authoritative source) -- structurally weak by the pack's own admitted design (pack.toml: 'following the literal-template-body pattern of packs/tcps-release-pack' -- whole pre-formatted blobs stored as grp:workflowBody/grp:artifactBody literals, not composed from finer facts) AND concretely stale, independently reconfirmed this pass: RELEASE_STANDING.json/.md and PUBLICATION_JUDGMENT.md's literal bodies all hardcode 'v26.7.20' while the live project version (Cargo.toml/ggen.toml [project].version) is '26.7.26' -- 6 patch releases stale -- and scripts/ci/guard-version-consistency.sh (this pack's own generated CI step, independently re-read this pass) does NOT catch it: that script only compares .specify/repo-facts.ttl/Cargo.toml/ggen.toml, never this pack's own generated artifacts. cap02 (generation surface) -- asymmetric: packs/ggen-release-pack/templates/*.tmpl (4 files) self-produce publish-candidate.yml/RELEASE_STANDING.json/RELEASE_STANDING.md/docs/PUBLICATION_JUDGMENT.md from a generic [packs]-composed consumer alone, but .github/workflows/marketplace-docs.yml needs a ROOT-repo-only declarative rule plus a Tera template living OUTSIDE the pack (.specify/templates/docs/ggen_marketplace_docs_workflow.yml.tera) -- a generic downstream consumer of just this pack cannot reproduce that 5th output. cap07 (generated docs) -- real: docs/PUBLICATION_JUDGMENT.md is genuinely SPARQL-SELECT-rendered from grp:PublicationJudgmentArtifact, confirmed current live. cap06 -- zero: no gates/ directory exists for this pack at all (unlike ggen-constitution-pack's 2, even-inert, gates)." ;
    l5p:missingCap l5p:cap01, l5p:cap02, l5p:cap05, l5p:cap06, l5p:cap08, l5p:cap09, l5p:cap10, l5p:cap11 ;
    l5p:nextPromotionObligation "Two concrete, disjoint next steps: (a) ggen_release_pack_workflow_e2e.rs is confirmed GREEN, not red (see currentCeiling correction) -- the real remaining gap is coverage breadth, not a failing test: extend real, dedicated proof coverage to the 4 outputs (publish-candidate.yml, RELEASE_STANDING.json, RELEASE_STANDING.md, docs/PUBLICATION_JUDGMENT.md) that currently have zero dedicated test coverage anywhere in the repo; (b) correct the 'v26.7.20' staleness in RELEASE_STANDING.json/.md/docs/PUBLICATION_JUDGMENT.md's literal ontology bodies to match the real project version (26.7.26, independently reconfirmed this pass), and either extend scripts/ci/guard-version-consistency.sh to check this pack's own artifacts or add a dedicated freshness gate -- currently nothing in the repo catches this drift. cap04 (fixed-point/erase-and-rebuild) stays genuinely UNVERIFIED this pass, not audited either way -- not claimed closed by omission." .

